<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex" />
    <title>OpenAgentDojo replay envelope · {{ handle }}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        color-scheme: light;
        --ink: #16181d;
        --muted: #5b6470;
        --rule: #cfd6df;
        --paper: #fafbfc;
        --accent: #2563eb;
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
        font-size: 14px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }
      main {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 32px 24px 48px;
      }
      header {
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
        padding-bottom: 16px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
      }
      header h1 {
        margin: 0 0 4px;
        font-size: 16px;
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      header .sub {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 12px;
      }
      h2 {
        margin: 24px 0 8px;
        font-size: 13px;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        color: var(--muted);
      }
      dl {
        margin: 0;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(140px, max-content) 1fr;
        gap: 4px 16px;
      }
      dt {
        color: var(--muted);
      }
      dd {
        margin: 0;
        word-break: break-all;
      }
      pre {
        background: #ffffff;
        border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        border-radius: 4px;
        padding: 12px;
        overflow-x: auto;
        font-size: 12.5px;
        white-space: pre-wrap;
        word-break: break-word;
      }
      .pill {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 1px 8px;
        border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        border-radius: 999px;
        font-size: 11px;
        color: var(--muted);
      }
      .score {
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .score .max {
        color: var(--muted);
        font-weight: 400;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
      footer {
        margin-top: 36px;
        padding-top: 12px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
        font-size: 11.5px;
        color: var(--muted);
      }
      a { color: var(--accent); }
      @media print {
        body { background: #fff; }
        pre { border-color: #999; }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <header>
        <h1>// openagentdojo · replay envelope</h1>
        <div class="sub">offline inspection page · no scripts, no remote calls</div>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>Subject</h2>
        <dl>
          <dt>handle</dt><dd>{{ handle }}</dd>
          <dt>mission</dt><dd>{{ mission_title }} <span class="pill">{{ mission_id }}</span></dd>
          <dt>submission_id</dt><dd>{{ submission_id }}</dd>
          <dt>graded_at</dt><dd>{{ graded_at }}</dd>
          <dt>rubric</dt><dd>{{ rubric_version }}</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Score</h2>
        <div class="score">{{ total_score }} <span class="max">/ {{ effective_max }}</span></div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Hash</h2>
        <pre>{{ verification_hash }}</pre>
        <h2>Signature</h2>
        <pre>{{ verification_signature }}</pre>
        <h2>Canonical URL</h2>
        <pre>{{ canonical_url }}</pre>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How to verify offline</h2>
        <p>
          The envelope above is the same dictionary the platform hashed at
          grade time. To re-derive the signature by hand, run:
        </p>
        <pre>
# 1. Compute the canonical hash:
#    sorted keys, separators=(',', ':'), ensure_ascii=False, UTF-8.
SHA-256(canonical_json(envelope)) === {{ verification_hash }}

# 2. Recompute the HMAC under the operator's VERIFY_SECRET:
HMAC-SHA256(VERIFY_SECRET, verification_hash) === {{ verification_signature }}</pre>
        <p>
          Recomputing the HMAC signature requires the operator's
          <code>VERIFY_SECRET</code>. As a self-check anyone can run,
          the SHA-256 of the canonical envelope must match
          <code>verification_hash</code> above — that step is
          reproducible from the bundle alone:
        </p>
        <pre>
# Linux / macOS recipe — no JavaScript, no remote calls:
python3 - &lt;&lt;'PY'
import json, hashlib, sys
env = json.load(open("replay.json"))["envelope"]
canon = json.dumps(env, sort_keys=True, separators=(",", ":"),
                   ensure_ascii=False).encode("utf-8")
print(hashlib.sha256(canon).hexdigest())
PY
# expected: {{ verification_hash }}</pre>
        <p>
          The bundle's <code>replay.json</code> carries the envelope plus the
          full supervision event stream that produced the score. The bundle's
          <code>README.md</code> documents the canonicalisation rules a third
          party can re-implement to reproduce the signature byte-for-byte
          once they obtain the secret from the operator.
        </p>
      </section>

      <footer>
        Generated by OpenAgentDojo · schema {{ schema_version }} ·
        replay {{ kind }} · exported {{ exported_at }}
      </footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
